1
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:55,740
=Sugar and Lies=
(A Different Her: The Women's Trilogy)

2
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:59,780
=Episode 5=
=Youth Staying in Aiye Town=

3
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:05,900
(Aiye South Street)

4
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,120
It feels like nothing here has changed.

5
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:19,680
Grandma passed away a few years ago.

6
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,720
Whenever I feel heavy inside,

7
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:22,960
I come here to clear my head.

8
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,360
Why not ask someone
to come with you?

9
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,200
Because some memories

10
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:34,720
are meant to be kept to myself.

11
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:48,000
Then should I be grateful to you

12
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,400
for sharing them with me?

13
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,480
No need to thank me.

14
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,280
It's just a contract.

15
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,880
It ends when the time's up.

16
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,080
What if I want to renew it?

17
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,160
Then I'm in for good.

18
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,670
B plus A.

19
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,000
(Math)
Look.

20
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,200
Guess what score I got.

21
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,640
Ninety-nine points.

22
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,880
So? Pretty impressive, right?

23
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,280
But still,

24
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,890
you should get a full score.

25
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,360
Why's that?

26
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,640
Because only a fuul score

27
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,960
makes you the most solid winner.

28
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:41,080
But what if I lose? What's the big deal?

29
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,160
You don't understand.

30
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,840
You can afford to lose,

31
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:46,680
but I can't.

32
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:50,600
Ding Daang.

33
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,200
Ding Daang.

34
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:04,960
This is...

35
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,040
Do you like it?

36
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,360
Wanna give it a try?

37
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,880
What are you trying to do?

38
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,560
No.

39
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,320
I don't like it.

40
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,920
You don't like it?

41
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,360
Or you just want to forget the past?

42
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:06,640
I don't really like these things.

43
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,990
I don't like looking back either.

44
00:04:08,990 --> 00:04:10,080
So let's not bring it up.

45
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,120
Ding Daang.

46
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,080
How about we start fresh?

47
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:20,920
Forget it then.

48
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,200
Such a beautiful day today.

49
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,240
Why'd you show up dressed like that?

50
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,360
I came to work with you.

51
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:51,240
If your dad sees you, we're in trouble.

52
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,160
It's fine.

53
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,840
He actually supports me earning money.

54
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,880
But honestly, this outfit looks awful.

55
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:01,280
Still, wearing the same thing as you

56
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,520
somehow makes it look nice.

57
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,680
Delicious Tong Sui for sale.

58
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,080
Don't miss out as you pass by.

59
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,000
Here, miss.

60
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,200
Delicious Tong Sui for sale.

61
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,880
Don't miss out as you pass by.

62
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:23,800
Don't miss it.

63
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,400
Ding Daang.

64
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,780
Do you remember this place?

65
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,080
I remember.

66
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,760
I used to

67
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:49,080
drink Tong Sui here
and sneak glances at you.

68
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,480
One day, I found a chance

69
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,790
to start a conversation with you.

70
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,640
I don't have a red dress.

71
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,400
So the teacher wouldn't let me
join the contest.

72
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,480
Miaomiao.

73
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:20,520
It's not like you have to
join these contests.

74
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,200
Let it be.

75
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,640
But none of them dance better than me.

76
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,440
If I get to compete,

77
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,200
I'd totally take first place.

78
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,480
Come on, Miaomiao.

79
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:32,560
You're always reasonable.

80
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,440
Just let it go, Miaomiao.

81
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,400
Okay?

82
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,760
Finish your drink
and get on with your homework.

83
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,720
I just want a red dress.

84
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,360
Why do others get one?

85
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,280
Why can't I get one?

86
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:03,680
Hey,

87
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,520
I've got a red dress at home.

88
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:06,880
It's too small for me now.

89
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,290
I'll bring it over for you tomorrow.

90
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:18,720
Oh right,

91
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,590
did Miaomiao come back with you?

92
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:24,040
I remember her being just like you,

93
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,640
good-looking and smart.

94
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,600
Not yet.

95
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,520
She's grown up now

96
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,320
and has changed quite a bit.

97
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:35,920
Just like this place.

98
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,880
Thank you.

99
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,200
Try it.

100
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,040
Does it still taste the same as before?

101
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,160
Some people and things can't be left behind

102
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,960
just because you want to.

103
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,120
Our minds can only hold so much.

104
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,280
Keep what's worth remembering.

105
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,140
Let go of what's better left behind.

106
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,840
Change what can be changed.

107
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:18,800
And accept...

108
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,840
what cannot be changed.

109
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:24,120
But life is yours to live.

110
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,680
So why not live a life

111
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,540
you truly want?

112
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:29,400
What about your life?

113
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,400
Is it what you want?

114
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,240
Yes.

115
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,800
And I'm still after more.

116
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,520
(Aming,)

117
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,680
(if the past really can't be revisited,)

118
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,920
(then maybe)

119
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:47,320
(we could still get to know each other)

120
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,240
(all over again as you wish.)

121
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,680
You're going to Mancheng for college.

122
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,460
(Qing Bei-Sen University)
Will you come back?

123
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,440
I'll wait for you there.

124
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:00,120
When I make some money one day,

125
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,880
I'll buy a big house in Mancheng

126
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,240
and bring Mom and my sister
to live with me.

127
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,240
But my grades are terrible.

128
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,480
I probably can't get into
a university in Mancheng.

129
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,240
Don't say that.

130
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,920
As long as you're willing to study,

131
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:21,560
I'll come back home

132
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:22,400
every summer break,

133
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,800
working part-time and tutoring you.

134
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,120
Really?

135
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,440
Yes.

136
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,040
Then...

137
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,520
when you go to Mancheng for college,

138
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,720
will you get a girlfriend?

139
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,200
Of course not.

140
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,280
Studies and making money

141
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,480
matters more.

142
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,720
But what if another girl

143
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,880
insists on chasing you?

144
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,560
Then I'll just

145
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,920
tell her I already have a girlfriend.

146
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,560
In a bit,

147
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:15,360
let's go check out Tianyi High School.

148
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,920
I'm good with anything.

149
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,000
I'll follow your lead.

150
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,960
The two of us at Tianyi High School

151
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,200
must be well-known, right?

152
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,160
One's famous for being good,

153
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,560
and the other for being trouble.

154
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,960
Is that Ding Daang?
The one with a major demerit record?

155
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,080
I heard her family's loaded.

156
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,160
Her dad got her a stepmom

157
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,280
and stopped caring about her.

158
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,280
No wonder she's always causing trouble.

159
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,000
Turns out she grew up without education.

160
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,080
Say that again, I dare you.

161
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,960
Did we say something we shouldn't?

162
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,280
He did find you a stepmother.

163
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,040
Let's go.

164
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,320
Back off.

165
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,150
Come with me.

166
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:01,080
Come on.

167
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,520
Watch your language.

168
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,480
Let me go.

169
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,560
Top student,

170
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,600
why help me out?

171
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,520
Aren't you afraid of their gossip?

172
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,040
Not at all.

173
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,560
Let me tell you something.

174
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:20,800
I don't need your help.

175
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,360
I'll deal with those crazy women.

176
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,160
But are you truly happy living like this?

177
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,200
Listen to me.

178
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,300
My mom passed away.

179
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:34,520
And my dad couldn't care less.

180
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,320
Do I even have the right to be happy?

181
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,760
I'll tutor you.

182
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,600
Once your grades are up,
the gossip stops.

183
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,800
Why are you helping me?

184
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:57,920
Because...

185
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,960
you helped me once too.

186
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,360
If you hadn't tutored me back then,

187
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,400
I wouldn't have made it to college.

188
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,120
Come to think of it...

189
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,560
If you hadn't lent me money often,

190
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:19,880
I might've dropped out of school
for work.

191
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:22,880
So what now?

192
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,080
How about we both say thanks
to each other?

193
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,520
Ding Daang,

194
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,120
thank you.

195
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,200
Really, thank you.

196
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,960
Where are you going?

197
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,560
The beach.

198
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:03,640
Do you remember who you spent

199
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,320
the first money you earned on?

200
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,000
Who?

201
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,320
I don't remember.

202
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,240
Where a man's money is,

203
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,480
where his love is.

204
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,200
I'm not after his money.

205
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,050
Maybe,

206
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,760
he's the one eyeing your money.

207
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,440
A room full of parasites.

208
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,880
After Miaomiao's breakup,

209
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:28,240
she hasn't been doing great.

210
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,040
You sure? You'll take the risk.

211
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,840
You're more cautious than me now.

212
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,320
The deposit's already in.

213
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,320
What's there to be scared of?

214
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:10,660
♪I forgot this is a movie meant for one♪

215
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:22,420
♪Somehow you're still here,
crying with me♪

216
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:28,810
♪They say♪

217
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:37,600
♪Lovers should never hold hands
while watching a sad movie♪

218
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:41,100
♪Some endings cannot be changed♪

219
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:47,270
♪They don't belong in sweet memories♪

220
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:54,410
♪I've already lost you♪

221
00:14:54,410 --> 00:14:59,890
♪Thinking of it takes my breath away♪

222
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:06,140
♪The movie ends, so many couples around♪

223
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:10,920
♪Yet none were ever like us♪

224
00:15:12,030 --> 00:15:16,060
♪The past will always pass♪

225
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:23,970
♪If you could still hold me tight
in your arms♪

226
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:27,690
♪I'd believe
that there are miracles in love♪

227
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:33,900
♪I'd prove
that I'm still in love with you♪

228
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:39,890
♪I've learned how to cherish
what we had♪

229
00:15:39,890 --> 00:15:46,150
♪But sadly, it's not you♪
